## Ownership Ambiguities

| Ambiguity | Current Handling | Required Next Action |
|---|---|---|
| Root global docs are local/unversioned. | Mark all root artifacts as local/unversioned. | Select versioned repository or continue explicit local-only governance. |
| Treasury/Financial Core is referenced as an authority but not represented as a distinct nucleus. | Map to Defi/Treasury for now. | Formalize treasury ownership before execution-sensitive planning. |
| Harmony DAO is an external dependency, not an Axodus nucleus. | Keep as supporting owner only. | Document external owner and approval path before plugin advancement. |
| Business-to-AxodusAPP ownership transfer for registry UI is not formalized. | Keep Business as data/model owner and AxodusAPP as presentation owner. | Create read-only consumer contract before implementation. |
| Wallet/account custody ownership crosses AxodusAPP, Core and product nuclei. | Keep wallet execution disabled. | Define wallet boundary contract before wallet-adjacent work. |

## Ownership Transfer Points

| Source Artifact | Transfer Target | Transfer Condition |
|---|---|---|
| Business governance readiness package | Governance | Governance scope is complete and requires owner review. |
| Business financial readiness package | Defi/Treasury | Treasury, settlement, custody, revenue or payout scope appears. |
| Business ACS readiness package | ACS | Provisioning, isolation, memory, agent or permission scope appears. |
| Business product catalog record | Documentation/AxodusAPP | Record is approved for read-only publication or presentation. |
| Portfolio dependency blocker | Owning nucleus | Blocker requires owner validation or resolution. |
| Execution-sensitive planning item | Owning execution nucleus plus review authority | Separate request is approved with explicit gates. |

## Boundary Statement

This matrix records ownership only. It does not authorize implementation, integration, production publication, governance execution, treasury movement, wallet signing, trading, DEX execution, marketplace settlement, mining payouts, lottery payouts, ACS provisioning, billing execution, production credentials or on-chain writes.
